@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Imito" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Imito runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  Imito offers two ways to play:

Normal game: Click on a tile, this will rotate it clockwise by 90
-----------  degrees.

Slide-em game: Click on a tile that is located next to the empty
-------------  space, even if that space has a coloured background
               pattern on it. If the tile you clicked on has a
               'link' pointing in that direction, the tile will
               move toward the empty space. Otherwise, that tile
               will rotate clockwise by 90 degrees.

  You can restart a game board by clicking on the 'Replay' button,
but be aware that the amount of moves you make for the current
game board is added up until you complete it...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

